<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE DEFENDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One portion of "The Defender" centered on the ethics/lack of ethics involved in 
The Times' running a specific story during the Bob's Big Boy murder trial 
several years ago. The D.A.'s office maintained that Abramson was using her 
husband's (Tim Rutten's) employment to further her own interests. 
</P>
<P>
Bringing the focus back to July, 1989, what could be more unethical than 
running Abramson's and Rutten's denials in the Los Angeles Times Magazine? 
Whether the charges were true or false, the question remains: Was "The 
Defender" an objective/impartial profile or a manipulative whitewash/defense of 
The Times? 
</P>
<P>
DAVID R. MOSS 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
