-- with its inherent conflicts of interest -- or a successful and growing 
insurance group." 
</P>
<P>
 -- Sir James Goldsmith, who is leading an investment group that bid $21.7 
billion for BAT Industries, referring to agreement he made to sell Farmers 
Group to French insurer Axa Midi if he succeeds in buying BAT. 
</P>
