<HEADLINE>
<P>
MALCOLM FORBES' BIRTHDAY BASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I opened my Sunday paper and thought they had delivered a copy of USA Today by 
mistake. Since when does a wealthy man's extravagant birthday party deserve 
front-page coverage in The Times? I found your choice of a photo, showing 
Malcolm Forbes and Elizabeth Taylor fronting two black men dressed as Nubian 
guards (or slaves), in extremely poor taste. Maybe the picture helped you sell 
newspapers. Mine went immediately in the garbage where it belonged. 
</P>
<P>
SHELLEY PRITIKIN 
</P>
<P>
Del Mar 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
