<HEADLINE>
<P>
MALCOLM FORBES' BIRTHDAY BASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Malcolm Forbes article (Aug. 20) points up the area of taxation most in 
need of reform -- corporate taxes. 
</P>
<P>
Virtually every doctor, every lawyer, everyone who can, incorporates. Why? 
Because it is infinitely more advantageous than being taxed as an individual. 
</P>
<P>
Time for Congress to start considering stepping on some corporate toes. A 
system that (would allow) Forbes to deduct his party expenses but doesn't allow 
an individual deduction for an IRA (let alone party expenses) is nowhere near 
being equitable. 
</P>
<P>
MICHAEL LAURENCE 
</P>
<P>
Sherman Oaks 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
