</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Giuseppe Attardi, professor of molecular biology at Caltech, has received the 
Antonio Feltrinelli International Prize for Medicine, a $70,000 award. Attardi 
received the award for his research in the mitochondrial genetic system in 
human cells. 
</P>
<P>
Jorge, Kita and Omar Montano, ages 6, 5 and 2, who live in West Covina, have 
received an Award for Youth Heroism from Westec Security Co. for rescuing their 
mother when she fell into the family swimming pool last June. 
</P>
<P>
John Merhaut and R. Dale Beland have been appointed to the Pasadena Parks and 
Recreation Commission. 
</P>
<P>
Carlene Clarke Miller has been named vice president and treasurer for Pomona 
College. Miller previously was assistant vice chancellor for budget and 
financial management at UCLA. 
</P>
<P>
William J. Weitekamp has been appointed chief executive officer of the San 
Gabriel Valley Health Centers Network of the county Department of Health 
Services. The network includes the El Monte Comprehensive Health Center and 
public health centers in Alhambra, Azusa, La Puente, Monrovia and Pomona. 
Weitekamp previously was administrator of the Pediatric Pavilion and 
Psychiatric Hospital at County-USC Medical Center. 
</P>
