<P>
A former Oakland School District payroll clerk is accused of using her Bible 
study group in a scheme to embezzle more than $24,000 from the district, police 
reported. Marie Louise Bell, 48, was arrested at her Richmond home on a warrant 
charging her with grand theft. Police said Bell masterminded a kickback scheme 
in which overtime and payroll records of some custodians were allegedly 
falsified. Officers said Bell apparently selected the custodians at random and 
on their paychecks would occasionally pay each of them a minimum of "several 
hundred dollars for unworked overtime." After the custodians received their 
first overtime payment, officer said Bell then contacted them and essentially 
said, "If you like what we're doing we can keep it up, but I get some." 
