<HEADLINE>
<P>
WINNING COLORS RETURNS A WINNER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
RATOGA SPRINGS, N.Y. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Winning Colors, the 1988 Kentucky Derby winner who underwent throat surgery 
three months ago, scored a 4 1/4-length victory in a six-furlong allowance for 
fillies and mares at Saratoga Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Winning Colors, trained by Wayne Lukas and ridden by Pat Day, was timed in 1:10 
1/5 and earned $24,600 from the purse of $41,000 for her first victory since 
the Derby. Winning Colors returned $2.80. 
</P>
<P>
Lukas said that the only visible effect of her surgery had been that "she was a 
little louder after lengthy gallops." 
</P>
<P>
Summer Squall, also ridden by Day, won the $234,000 Hopeful Stakes for 
2-year-olds later in the program. 
</P>
<P>
The son of Storm Bird-Weekend Surprise remained undefeated in five career 
starts, the last four of which have been stakes, covering 6 1/2 furlongs in 
1:16 4/5. Summer Squall returned $3.80. 
</P>
</TEXT>
