<HEADLINE>
<P>
CURRENT PAPERBACKS: SPACE SHUTTLE: THE QUEST CONTINUES BY GEORGE TORRES 
(PRESIDIO PRESS: $12.95, ILLUSTRATED) 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
George Torres writes about the U.S. Space Program and the shuttle program in 
particular with the relentless boosterism of a used-car salesman describing the 
bargains on his lot. He ignores the questions about overspecialization raised 
by critics of the shuttle, much as he ignores the enormous and, in the opinion 
of many experts, insurmountable problems of creating a functional SDI system. 
The illustrations help redeem the text, especially the photographs from the 
Apollo missions, which recall the excitement and hope that galvanized the 
nation only 20 years ago. 
