<HEADLINE>
<P>
REV. LOU SHELDON AND RIGHTS OF HOMOSEXUALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sheldon's Commentary that homosexuality should not have a minority status is 
fatally flawed because if the average homosexual is a walking "tropical island 
of exotic diseases," doomed to "a life of self-destructive perversion," then 
why would anyone care to become homosexual? 
</P>
<P>
People do not necessarily choose to become homosexual and face the terrible 
discrimination, injury, disease and death. Rather, they are most often born 
that way, having little or no control over the constant uphill battle they must 
face against misguided religious fanatics. Hitler tried the same tactics in 
Germany with minorities, finally murdering thousands of homosexuals, but 
right-thinking men and women in the long run righted the injustice. The same 
will prevail in this case and every case where blind bigotry rears its ugly 
head. 
</P>
<P>
Sheldon may have homosexuality denied a minority status today; however, one 
shining day, society will grant all of its citizens equal rights and protect 
them to grow to their full potential. 
</P>
<P>
RICHARD MOWERY 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
