<HEADLINE>
<P>
UCLA STUDENT WINS DESIGN COMPETITION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Andres Jost, a student in the interior design program at UCLA Extension, has 
taken first place in the student design category of the American Society of 
Interior Designers/Du Pont annual Corian national design competition. 
</P>
<P>
Corian is a solid, non-porous surfacing material often used for countertops, 
sinks, shower walls and wainscoting. Jost's design for a coffee table sculpted 
form Corian and accented with metal and glass was hailed as "exceptionally 
imaginative" by the judging committee. 
</P>
<P>
Jost was given the award and a check for $1,000 at the society's annual 
conference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA082789-0176 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 100044 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
August 27, 1989, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
