<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMERCIAL SCENE; 
</P>
<P>
IDM CORP. TO DEVELOP $250-MILLION PROJECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Long Beach-based IDM Corp. has signed an agreement to develop a $250-million 
mixed-use project on land leased from the Riverside Community College District. 
</P>
<P>
Known as La Sierra, the project will be built over an eight- to 10-year period 
on 119 acres just off California 91 at the La Sierra Avenue exit in Riverside. 
A ground breaking is expected within the next 12 months. 
</P>
<P>
Plans call for 200,000 square feet of retail space, five restaurants, a 
230-room hotel, college administrative offices and conference center, 261,000 
square feet of office space, and about 1,050 apartments. 
</P>
