<P>
AIRPORT ATRIUM UNDER CONSTRUCTION IN TORRANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Construction has begun on the $15-million Airport Atrium, a 100,000-square-foot 
office building on the northern edge of Torrance Municipal Airport. 
</P>
<P>
The four-story structure, at 2780 Skypark Drive, will have an atrium that runs 
from the ground floor to the top of the building. The exterior of the complex 
will have narrow bands of white concrete alternating with wider bands of blue 
glass. 
</P>
<P>
Architect is the Nadel Partnership of Santa Monica and developer is 
Torrance-based Real Property Resources Inc. The Seeley Co. of Torrance is 
leasing agent and the Los Angeles office of Koll Construction Co. is general 
contractor. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
