<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMERCIAL SCENE; 
</P>
<P>
WORK STARTED ON BUSINESS COMPLEX IN SIMI VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Construction has begun on the $11-million Sanport Business Centre, a 
183,900-square-foot complex in Simi Valley. 
</P>
<P>
The 10-acre project will be composed of five industrial and 
research-and-development buildings ranging from 26,000 to 86,000 square feet. 
It is inside the Simi Valley Commerce Center, on Ward Avenue about three blocks 
south of California 118. 
</P>
<P>
Newport Beach-based Sanport Development is building the facility. Ware &amp; 
Malcomb Inc. is the architect, Oltmans Construction Co. is general contractor 
and Grubb &amp; Ellis is exclusive leasing agent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
