<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMERCIAL SCENE; 
</P>
<P>
CONSTRUCTION UNDER WAY ON MURRIETA SHOP CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Construction has begun on Murrieta Town Center, the largest shopping center in 
Murrieta Hot Springs. 
</P>
<P>
The $90-million, 500,000-square-foot project of Crossroads Development is 
already 90% leased, with such anchors as Hughes Market, Home Club, Payless 
Drugs, Edwards Theaters, Big 5, Chief Auto Parts, Del Taco and Denny's 
Restaurant. 
</P>
<P>
The project, the first of four planned by Crossroads in the area, is located at 
the intersection of Highway 215, Interstate 215 and Murrieta Hot Springs Road. 
</P>
