<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMERCIAL SCENE; 
</P>
<P>
HOTEL RENOVATION BEGINS AT SOUTH COAST WESTIN HOTEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tishman Construction Corp. of California has begun a 1-year, $10.5-million 
renovation of the Westin South Coast Plaza Hotel, 666 Anton Blvd., Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
All 390 rooms at the 14-year-old hotel are being upgraded, as are the main 
ballroom, lobbies, cafe and most other common areas. A new boardroom will be 
added on the third floor and an executive lounge with business-related services 
will be built on the 15th floor. 
</P>
<P>
Leo A. Daly is architect of the project. Interior design and space-planning is 
being done by FORMA Design Group. 
</P>
