SOURCE: California Commission on Campaign Financing data analysis 
</P>
<P>
GARDENA FACTS 
</P>
<P>
* Local government structure: Charter drafted in 1930; weak mayor system; four 
city council members elected at-large to four-year terms; mayor elected 
citywide to two-year terms; city clerk elected; city attorney apointed by 
council. 
</P>
<P>
* City budget: $30 million (fiscal year 1988-1989) 
</P>
<P>
* City facts: Population (1989): 50,900; area: 5.36 square miles; registered 
voters (April 1989): 20,535; voter turnout (April 1988): 27% 
</P>
</TEXT>
