<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFING: EVENTS IN THE NEWS THIS WEEK. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An 11-member citizens advisory group will meet at the Trabuco Canyon fire 
station Monday and Wednesday to consider a county proposal to allow 1,700 new 
homes and a new two-lane road to be built in the Foothill-Trabuco area. The 
controversial plan is aimed at regulating growth in a 6,500-acre swatch of 
backcountry northeast of Mission Viejo. The advisory group, made up of local 
residents and property owners, will either endorse or reject the plan before it 
goes to the county Planning Commission and ultimately the Board of Supervisors 
for a vote. The plan has already drawn fire from both environmentalists and 
developers. 
</P>
