<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFING: EVENTS IN THE NEWS THIS WEEK. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Meadowlark Airport in Huntington Beach, after years of wrangling with the city 
over safety and other issues, will close Friday to make way for condominiums 
and a shopping center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA082789-0203 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 100324 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
August 27, 1989, Sunday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Metro; Part 2; Page 3; Column 4; Metro Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
134 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
11-MONTH-OLD BOY DROWNS IN POOL AT BUENA PARK HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An 11-month-old Buena Park boy who had been playing in the back yard of his 
home wandered through a swimming pool security gate and drowned Saturday, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Thomas Lorey was discovered by his father about 12:15 p.m. floating face down 
in the family's pool at 8319 Mars Drive and was rushed by paramedics to Humana 
Hospital-West Anaheim, where he was pronounced dead at 1:12 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
The boy's father, Michael Lorey, told authorities that Thomas had been playing 
in the back yard with his sister and wandered away. 
</P>
<P>
It was not immediately known if the gate to the pool was locked at the time of 
the accident. 
</P>
<P>
Lorey pulled the boy from the water and began cardiopulmonary resuscitation, 
which was unsuccessfully continued by paramedics. 
</P>
<P>
The family declined to discuss the accident Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
