<HEADLINE>
<P>
ON THE COVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cable television strikes up "A Conversation With Dinah" this week. 
</P>
<P>
Dinah Shore, who has hosted talk shows on network TV and in syndication, 
returns for a new round of celebrity chats Monday at 5 p.m. on the Nashville 
Network. 
</P>
<P>
In the debut of her half-hour series, Shore talks with Nancy Reagan. It's the 
first interview the former First Lady has given since leaving the White House. 
Other guests this week are Betty White (Tuesday); John Forsythe (Wednesday); 
Angie Dickinson (Thursday); Rosemary Clooney (Friday) and Jack Lemmon (Saturday 
at 7 p.m.). 
</P>
<P>
Starting next week, the series will be shown Tuesdays and Thursdays at 5 p.m. 
and Saturdays at 7 p.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, COLOR, Dinah Shore Steve Fontanini / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
